      l4windBtn:"🎤 Enable mic & prepare to sail",
      l4set:"The sail swells… setting sail 🌊",
      l4oar:"🚣 Row out (tap repeatedly)",
      l4oarPrefix:"rowing: ",
      l4oarSet:"You row out… setting sail 🌊",
      l5tag:"SET SAIL · the first channel",
      l5riddle:"✦ Nothing but dark sea. The guide is in the sky.\nConnect the scattered stars with your finger to draw the way.",
      l5hint:"Hint: drag to *connect all the stars*. (stuck? tap ‘redraw’)",
      l5clear:"↺ redraw",
      l5reveal:"polaris",
      l6tag:"FOG 1 · shelter the flame",
      l6riddle:"🌫️ The fog is thick. A small lantern wavers in the wind.\nCup it with two fingers and keep the flame alive.",
      l6hint:"Hint: bring two fingers around the lantern to *shelter* it. (one hand? press & hold ‘shield’ below)",
      l6shelterPrefix:"shelter: ",
      l6shelterBtn:"🤚 shield with one hand (hold)",
      l6set:"The flame holds steady… a warmth stays beside you 🕯️",
      l7tag:"STORM 1 · row",
      l7riddle:"🌊 The waves are fierce — you can't cross alone.\nTwo find the rhythm: pull the oars, left and right in turn.",
      l7hint:"Hint: tap the *glowing* oar, alternating left and right.",
      l7rowPrefix:"progress: ",
      l7set:"Through the storm… far off, stars appear ✦",
      l8tag:"FAREWELL · the recital",
      l8hint:"Hint: *press and hold* — keep holding, all the way to the end.",
      l8btn:"🤲 hold gently — to the end",
      l8lines:["Cup the last light, gently, in both hands.","Across the water — hand the lantern over.","Turn the empty boat's bow back toward home.","As you drift away, add one last breath to the sail."],
      l8end:"Go well. I'll keep this side.",
      doneTitle:"Voyage 🌅",
      doneBody:"It reached. The lantern blinks on the far shore,<br>and the empty boat turns home — alone.",
      doneEnd:"— end of the first voyage · fin —",
      sc_tutorial:"The First Night", hubTitle:"Crossroads",
      sc_snow:"Snow Lake — ferry the old dog",
      snow1tag:"SNOW LAKE · the shivering one", snow1riddle:"❄️ A lake under first snow. An old dog shivers, still.\nRest your hand beside it — long and quiet.", snow1press:"rest — your hand", snow1reveal:"warmth", snow1hint:"Hint: *press and hold* to share warmth.", snow_a1:"warmth",
      snow2tag:"SNOW LAKE · still ripples", snow2riddle:"🚣 The dog has boarded. Cross the still lake.\nPull the oars, left and right in turn.", snow2hint:"Hint: tap the *glowing* oar, alternating.",
      snowDoneTitle:"The Far Shore ❄️",
      snowDoneBody:"The old dog rested its chin on the bow, watching you the whole way across.<br>Stepping onto dry ground, it looked back — just once. With the eyes of someone you've lived beside for years.<br>\"You won't be cold now.\"",
      snowCoda:"As you turn the boat, a leash lies on the floor. Not slipped loose — left behind. For you.",
      snowDoneEnd:"— Snow Lake · fin —",
      sc_dawn:"Dawn River — ferry the child",
      dawnTag:"DAWN RIVER · side by side", dawnRiddle:"🌫️ The river at dawn, the fog lifting. The child who is leaving has boarded.\nMatch the child's rhythm — pull both oars *together*.", dawnHint:"Hint: press both oars *at once* (two fingers). One hand? tap ‘row together’ below.",
      rpPrefix:"progress: ", rpSet:"Across the river… the child looks ahead 🌅", rpSyncBtn:"🤲 row together (tap)",
      foldTag:"DAWN RIVER · a paper boat", foldRiddle:"🌫️ Nothing to give the leaving child. Just one worn sheet left by the river.\nWith your fingertips, slowly — *swipe* to fold it into a little boat.", foldHint:"Hint: *swipe* across the paper to fold, one crease at a time (three).",
      foldPrefix:"fold: ", foldSet:"A little boat, finished 🛶",
      dawnDoneTitle:"The Far Shore 🌅",
      dawnDoneBody:"The moment the child touched dry ground — they ran ahead. Without looking back, not once.<br>That was the good kind. Nothing to look back for means somewhere better is waiting.<br>\"Grow well there, too.\"",
      dawnCoda:"A paper boat drifted at your feet. Smaller and clumsier than the one you folded — made to look like you. Not left behind, but made, and left for you.",
      dawnDoneEnd:"— Dawn River · fin —",
      sc_lantern:"Lantern Harbor — ferry the fading one",
      emberTag:"LANTERN HARBOR · the ember", emberRiddle:"🪔 A harbor full of lanterns. Someone's memory is going out.\nCarry the ember — without lifting your hand, slowly — to the empty lantern.", emberHint:"Hint: *hold and drag slowly*. Lift your hand and it goes out.",
      emberPrefix:"carrying: ", emberSet:"The empty lantern catches light 🪔", emberOut:"The ember went out… again",
      lanternDoneTitle:"The Far Shore 🪔",
      lanternDoneBody:"Reaching the far shore, they looked at you — but did not know you. They had already forgotten too much.<br>And that was all right. It is lighter, for the one who forgets.<br>\"Even if you forget — I'll keep a place for you here.\"",
      lanternCoda:"Back in the harbor, one more lantern was lit. Its name tag empty — its flame the one you carried over. Forgotten, yet the place remains.",
      lanternDoneEnd:"— Lantern Harbor · fin —",
      sc_reunion:"Reunion — The Kept Place on the Far Shore",
      reunionTag:"REUNION · two lights", reunionRiddle:"✨ Someone who crossed before is still waiting.\nBring your light — without hurry, very slowly — to theirs.", reunionHint:"Hint: *hold and drag very slowly*. Rush or lift, and it stops.",
      reunionPrefix:"drawing near: ", reunionSet:"The two lights meet ✨", reunionOut:"It stopped… again, slowly",
      reunionDoneTitle:"The Far Shore ✨",
      reunionDoneBody:"The boat touches shore. The rocking stills.<br>They step off. Unhurried.",
      reunionSeq:["On the far side, a single light.","Small. An old light.","They stop.","…They know that light.","One step.","The light wavers. As if it looked back.","Another step.","Far off, someone rises.","From a place they'd sat a long time.","Their pace quickens.","No calling out. No need.","The gap between the two lights narrows.","Narrows,","and narrows,","and meets.","The space someone had kept open.","This time, that kept place had been waiting for them.","The two lights become one.","Not brighter. Only warmer.","The boatman watches.","Until the crossing is wholly done.","And quietly, nods."],
      reunionCoda:"He turns the empty bow toward home.",
      reunionDoneEnd:"Always there first; still there after. — fin —",
